SUMMARY:"Groovin' and 'Couvin" 2.0 Vancouver Downtown\, Waterfront & Renaissance Trail 
DESCRIPTION:Portland City Trail Walking Group\n**DESCRIPTION**: Let’s meet for a trek along the periphery of Fort Vancouver\, the Vancouver Land Bridge\, downtown and the waterfront\, replete with some vibrant art installations and murals along the way. Shout out to local talent RANDY for designing and leading this walk.\n\n***RSVP ETIQUETTE: Thank you in advance for changing your RSVP from "Going" to "Not Going" or drop a note in the chat if your plans change.***\n\n**DISTANCE**: About 6 miles.\n\n**PARKING AND MEET AT:** Near Red Robin\; park at or nearby in large Fred Meyer lot. 2410 Columbia House Blvd\, Vancouver\, WA 98661\n\n**LAUNCH TIME**: 10:00 A.M.\n\n**FITNESS LEVEL**: Expect a moderate pace for this mostly flat and paved urban walk.\n\n**ATTIRE**: Bring your layers and adventurous spirit.\n\n**GUESTS**: Guests welcome! Please input their name on the website when you RSVP.\n\n**REPAST OPTION (or not):** Group preference.
